      "writtenOn": "2016-04-07T19:14:37Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we really need these restrictions? If the programmer has an std::multimap or a custom implementation of something that behaves like a map or set they won\u0027t be able to use these functions, this seems to go against the idea of having templates as a way of allowing anything that behaves the right way.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 30,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 40,
        "endChar": 73
      },
      "revId": "78428f1aaca7780b40c706bd00458e230655a7b7",
